                <h3>
                  <span class="octicon octicon-book"></span>
                  /home/garaemon/ros/hydro/src/jsk-ros-pkg/jsk_common/jsk_network_tools/README.md
                </h3>

              <div class="markdown-body entry-content">
                <h1>
<a id="user-content-jsk_network_tools" class="anchor" href="#jsk_network_tools" aria-hidden="true"><span class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>jsk_network_tools</h1>

<h2>
<a id="user-content-limited-network-communication" class="anchor" href="#limited-network-communication" aria-hidden="true"><span class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>Limited Network Communication.</h2>

<p>The goal of silverhammer is to provide communication between two different ROS networks over limited network.
<a href="images/silverhammer_overview.svg" target="_blank"><img src="images/silverhammer_overview.svg" alt="" style="max-width:100%;"></a></p>

<p>Currently jsk_network_tools supports two types of limited network model:</p>

<ol>
<li>Bidirectional and narrow network.</li>
<li>Unidirectional and intermittent network.</li>
</ol>

<p>These two models are strongly inspired by <a href="http://theroboticschallenge.org/">DRC-final</a>.</p>

<h3>
<a id="user-content-bidirectional-and-narrow-network" class="anchor" href="#bidirectional-and-narrow-network" aria-hidden="true"><span class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>Bidirectional and narrow network</h3>

<p>jsk_network_tools provides <code>silverhammer_lowspeed_gateway.py</code>, which is
a gateway between two different ROS network over narrow network.</p>

<p>Concenpt of <code>silverhammer_lowspeed_gateway.py</code> is:</p>

<ol>
<li>
<p>Use UDP prevent hand-shaking and re-sending.</p>

<p>Simply use UDP protocol with fixed rate.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Serialize data into small format.</p>

<p>Automatically generate serialization format from definition of ROS message.
However, this serialization only supports the simplest message definition.
Limitation of the serialization are:</p>

<ol>
<li>No nested field is allowed.</li>
<li>No variable length array is allowed.</li>
<li>
<code>string</code> is not supported.</li>
<li>
<code>int8</code> is not supported.</li>
</ol>
</li>
</ol>

              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

    function showCanonicalImages() {
      var images = document.getElementsByTagName('img');
      if (!images) {
        return;
      }
      for (var index = 0; index < images.length; index++) {
        var image = images[index];
        if (image.getAttribute('data-canonical-src')) {
          image.src = image.getAttribute('data-canonical-src');
        }
      }
    }
    function scrollToHash() {
      if (location.hash && !document.querySelector(":target")) {
        var elements = document.getElementsByName('user-content-' + location.hash.slice(1));
        if (elements.length > 0) {
          elements[elements.length - 1].scrollIntoView();
        }
      }
    }
    window.onhashchange = function() {
      scrollToHash();
    }
    window.onload = function() {
      scrollToHash();
    }
    showCanonicalImages();
  </script>

                <h3>

                </h3>

              <div class="markdown-body entry-content">
                <h1>
<a id="user-content-jsk_network_tools" class="anchor" href="#jsk_network_tools" aria-hidden="true"><span class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>jsk_network_tools</h1>

<h2>
<a id="user-content-limited-network-communication" class="anchor" href="#limited-network-communication" aria-hidden="true"><span class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>Limited Network Communication.</h2>

<p>The goal of silverhammer is to provide communication between two different ROS networks over limited network.
<a href="images/silverhammer_overview.svg" target="_blank"><img src="images/silverhammer_overview.svg" alt="" style="max-width:100%;"></a></p>

<p>Currently jsk_network_tools supports two types of limited network model:</p>

<ol>
<li>Bidirectional and narrow network.</li>
<li>Unidirectional and intermittent network.</li>
</ol>

<p>These two models are strongly inspired by <a href="http://theroboticschallenge.org/">DRC-final</a>.</p>

<h3>
<a id="user-content-bidirectional-and-narrow-network" class="anchor" href="#bidirectional-and-narrow-network" aria-hidden="true"><span class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>Bidirectional and narrow network</h3>

<p>jsk_network_tools provides <code>silverhammer_lowspeed_gateway.py</code>, which is
a gateway between two different ROS network over narrow network.</p>

<p>Concenpt of <code>silverhammer_lowspeed_gateway.py</code> is:</p>

<ol>
<li>
<p>Use UDP prevent hand-shaking and re-sending.</p>

<p>Simply use UDP protocol with fixed rate.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Serialize data into small format.</p>

<p>Automatically generate serialization format from definition of ROS message.
However, this serialization only supports the simplest message definition.
Limitation of the serialization are:</p>

<ol>
<li>No nested field is allowed.</li>
<li>No variable length array is allowed.</li>
<li>
<code>string</code> is not supported.</li>
<li>
<code>int8</code> is not supported.</li>
</ol>
</li>
</ol>

              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

    function showCanonicalImages() {
      var images = document.getElementsByTagName('img');
      if (!images) {
        return;
      }
      for (var index = 0; index < images.length; index++) {
        var image = images[index];
        if (image.getAttribute('data-canonical-src')) {
          image.src = image.getAttribute('data-canonical-src');
        }
      }
    }
    function scrollToHash() {
      if (location.hash && !document.querySelector(":target")) {
        var elements = document.getElementsByName('user-content-' + location.hash.slice(1));
        if (elements.length > 0) {
          elements[elements.length - 1].scrollIntoView();
        }
      }
    }
    window.onhashchange = function() {
      scrollToHash();
    }
    window.onload = function() {
      scrollToHash();
    }
    showCanonicalImages();
  </script>

              <div class="markdown-body entry-content">
                <h1>
<a id="user-content-jsk_network_tools" class="anchor" href="#jsk_network_tools" aria-hidden="true"><span class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>jsk_network_tools</h1>

<h2>
<a id="user-content-limited-network-communication" class="anchor" href="#limited-network-communication" aria-hidden="true"><span class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>Limited Network Communication.</h2>

<p>The goal of silverhammer is to provide communication between two different ROS networks over limited network.
<a href="images/silverhammer_overview.svg" target="_blank"><img src="images/silverhammer_overview.svg" alt="" style="max-width:100%;"></a></p>

<p>Currently jsk_network_tools supports two types of limited network model:</p>

<ol>
<li>Bidirectional and narrow network.</li>
<li>Unidirectional and intermittent network.</li>
</ol>

<p>These two models are strongly inspired by <a href="http://theroboticschallenge.org/">DRC-final</a>.</p>

<h3>
<a id="user-content-bidirectional-and-narrow-network" class="anchor" href="#bidirectional-and-narrow-network" aria-hidden="true"><span class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>Bidirectional and narrow network</h3>

<p>jsk_network_tools provides <code>silverhammer_lowspeed_gateway.py</code>, which is
a gateway between two different ROS network over narrow network.</p>

<p>Concenpt of <code>silverhammer_lowspeed_gateway.py</code> is:</p>

<ol>
<li>
<p>Use UDP prevent hand-shaking and re-sending.</p>

<p>Simply use UDP protocol with fixed rate.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Serialize data into small format.</p>

<p>Automatically generate serialization format from definition of ROS message.
However, this serialization only supports the simplest message definition.
Limitation of the serialization are:</p>

<ol>
<li>No nested field is allowed.</li>
<li>No variable length array is allowed.</li>
<li>
<code>string</code> is not supported.</li>
<li>
<code>int8</code> is not supported.</li>
</ol>
</li>
</ol>

              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

    function showCanonicalImages() {
      var images = document.getElementsByTagName('img');
      if (!images) {
        return;
      }
      for (var index = 0; index < images.length; index++) {
        var image = images[index];
        if (image.getAttribute('data-canonical-src')) {
          image.src = image.getAttribute('data-canonical-src');
        }
      }
    }
    function scrollToHash() {
      if (location.hash && !document.querySelector(":target")) {
        var elements = document.getElementsByName('user-content-' + location.hash.slice(1));
        if (elements.length > 0) {
          elements[elements.length - 1].scrollIntoView();
        }
      }
    }
    window.onhashchange = function() {
      scrollToHash();
    }
    window.onload = function() {
      scrollToHash();
    }
    showCanonicalImages();
  </script>
